    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-13T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-13T19:00:00-05:00" n="1075"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1075">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.00/176: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-13T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 13, 1943—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1741. Please reply to the telegram from the Egyptian Prime Minister and Ministry
                    for Foreign Affairs quoted in your 2040, November 11, 8 p.m. stating that this
                    Government has welcomed this expression of the views of the Egyptian Government
                    and informing them of the substance of this Government’s representations to the
                    French National Committee as set forth in the Department’s recent telegrams to
                    Algiers and Beirut, repeated to you in Department’s 1705, November 9, midnight;
                    1731, November 12, 10 p.m.; and 1734, November 12, midnight.<note n="32"
                        xml:id="d1075fn32">See footnote 8, <ref target="#pg_1009">p. 1009</ref>;
                        footnote 25, <ref target="#pg_1021">p. 1021</ref>; and footnote 27, <ref
                            target="#pg_1022">p. 1022</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="1040" n="1028" xml:id="pg_1028"/>
                <p>Your 2041, November 11, 9 p.m. Please make similar communication to King.</p>
                <p>Sent to Cairo. Repeated to London, Algiers and Beirut.<note n="33"
                        xml:id="d1075fn33">As telegrams Nos. 7197, 2154, and 275,
                        respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
